This paper is likely to belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) category as it deals with scheduling algorithms for cloud providers. It could also belong to the Computer Communications and Networks (cs.CC) category as it discusses new cloud usage and payment models. The Operating Systems (cs.OS) category is also a possibility as the paper deals with resource provisioning and utilization. The Networked and Internet-based Systems (cs.NI) category is relevant as the paper discusses virtual machines and their lifetimes. Finally, the Systems and Control (cs.SY) category could be relevant as the paper discusses the correctness and performance overhead of the proposed scheduler.
